   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Eighty-nine A NEW AND LIVING WAY Scripture: Heb 10:20 The path of man s living The path of man s living is a path that is far away from God.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>This path is a path of committing sins.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>This path is also a path of going into death.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>God s saving way The Lord Jesus bore man s sins and died for man.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The Lord resurrected and imparted His life into man.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>A new and living way God s saving way is a way God has prepared for man.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>This way is through the Lord s crucifixion, the shedding of His blood, and through His resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>This way enables man to come near to God.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>This way was never open before, so it is a new way; and this way is in Christ s resurrection life, so it is also a living way.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>This way does not have the hindrance of sin; rather, it has the power of life, drawing us close to God.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>This way not only brings man near to God, but also allows man to be one with God.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Not only can man enjoy all the blessings that God bestows upon him, but he can also enjoy God Himself.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>How to partake of this way</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Develop this point.</S>
   </TEXT>
